      <p parentName="blockquote">{`Kwikswap---and other constant product markets---appear to work well in practice despite their simplicity. In this paper, we give a simple formal analysis of constant product markets and their generalizations, showing that, under some common conditions, these markets must closely track the reference market price. We also show that Kwikswap satisfies many other desirable properties and numerically demonstrate, via a large-scale agent-based simulation, that Kwikswap is stable under a wide range of market conditions.`}</p>
